Getting to know CAD interface. Terminology. Drawing field, navigating on the drawing. Lines and points, coordinates, direct distance. Simpler means for drawing: line, sphere, rectangle, polygon. Simpler modification tools: moving, copying, rotating, arrays. Texts and dimensions. Drawing on different layers. Compound lines and splines, modifying compound lines. Model dimensions and paper dimensions. Blocks and editing them. Hatching. Title block. Setting the drawings for printing.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Acquire the knowledge and skills necessary for using the technical drawing CADprogram in the elementary level.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students:
-	acquires the basic principles of drawing with CAD;
-	acquires the basic commands;
-	can draw according to sample tasks;
-	can prepare drawings of different objects;
-	can finalize drawings;
-	develop the skills for presenting and providing arguments for the drawing.
